Not my work, just wanted to share and get it off my phone.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ksnkdd7</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[blueipDriver]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The unlikely story of two incredible Supermen</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/og4RDr4</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VlE5Q5n.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The iconic Robin Williams and Christopher Reeve were the best of friends. The two met in 1973 at Juillard.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/p9LM1qT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>In his autobiography, Reeve later wrote of Williams: "The first person I met at Juilliard was the other advanced student, a short, stocky, long-haired fellow from Marin County, California, who wore tie-dyed shirts with track suit bottoms and talked a mile a minute."</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1tW1XWM.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>“I’d never seen so much energy contained in one person. He was like an un-tied balloon that had been inflated & immediately released. I watched in awe as he virtually caromed off the walls of the classrooms & hallways. To say that he was ‘on’ would be a major understatement."</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/0QlyLCa.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>In 1978, a 24-yr old Reeve was cast in Superman, which made him a global star. The same year, Williams appeared in Mork & Mindy, which at its peak had a weekly audience of sixty million. The two went on to have storied careers in film and entertainment, & remained in touch.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/k4IWR8p.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Reeve was also an avid sportsman. In 1995, he was thrown off a horse in a competition. He suffered a serious cervical spinal injury that left him paralyzed from the neck down, and unable to breathe without a ventilator. As the accident had damaged his vertebrae, Reeve was forced to undergo a life-threatening surgery. He later wrote: “I already knew that I had only a 50-50 chance of surviving the surgery. I lay on my back, frozen, unable to avoid thinking the darkest thoughts.”</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/r6OdF1N.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>As he lay in pain, a person with a blue scrub hat & a yellow surgical gown & glasses entered his room. He spoke in a Russian accent & insisted that Reeve turn over and have a proctology exam. Reeve was very surprised but soon realized who it was.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/BBOON73.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>It was Williams, reprising his character from a recent film. Reeve later wrote, "For the first time since the accident, I laughed. My old friend had helped me know that somehow I was going to be okay." The two remained the best of friends throughout Reeve’s final years.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wOMeHT3.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>In 2004, Reeve passed away. The next year, Robin Williams was honored by the HFPA with the Cecil B. DeMille Award in 2005.  He dedicated the lifetime achievement award to his friend.
The speech: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j0hYctu65yw
Another story that alludes to Robin having paid for some of Christopher Reeve's medical expenses: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_UyT7NHYFEw</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/og4RDr4</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[LogicDude]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Doctor trying to explain things to government officials</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/NW7gdgs</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/U0bytqD.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Dr. Karen Berg trying to explain fetal development to KY Senators</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/NW7gdgs</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[lucyblues]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Sportsmanship</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/zvdL7Rx</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xgCChCn.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/zvdL7Rx</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[awfulmemeuser]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Happy Hippo</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/GoRW4XN</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jGCXlFu.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/GoRW4XN</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[mfrybeasley]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>&quot;No&quot;</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/SM5o6vP</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/zI5i0HO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/SM5o6vP</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[TiredSnowball]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>A worthy prey</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/WDuHRRw</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/mWf4Wu8.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></descriptio